snippet: Hassan Sheikh Mohamud, who was elected Monday, was speaking to reporters when three bombers attacked, killing at least four people.
abstract: Three suicide bombers attack the temporary residence of Somali Pres Hassan Sheik Mohamud as he is giving a news conference, killing an African Union soldier but failing to assassinate any political leaders; Mohamud, had only just been elected to his post by the newly created Parliament, taking the helm of a fledgling government that is supposed to represent a tangible step toward permanent governance in a country that has been without it for more than 20 years.
lead_paragraph: Hassan Sheikh Mohamud, who was elected Monday, was speaking to reporters when three bombers attacked, killing at least four people.

headline.seo: Somalia President Not Hurt by Suicide Bombings
headline.main: Somalia’s New President Survives Suicide Bombings
headline.print_headline: Somalia’s New President Survives Suicide Bombings
